question:
Consider the following code snippet. What is the logged output when the button is clicked?

```html
<button id="myBtn">Click Me</button>
<script>
  const button = document.getElementById('myBtn');

  button.addEventListener('click', function() {
    console.log(this.id);
  });

  button.addEventListener('click', () => {
    console.log(this.id);
  });
</script>```
